Established in 1927, Performance Sports Group Ltd. (formerly Bauer Performance Sports) designs, manufactures and markets performance sports equipment and related apparel under the leading brands Bauer Hockey, Mission Roller Hockey and Maverik Lacrosse. The company's products are available in over… MoreEstablished in 1927, Performance Sports Group Ltd. (formerly Bauer Performance Sports) designs, manufactures and markets performance sports equipment and related apparel under the leading brands Bauer Hockey, Mission Roller Hockey and Maverik Lacrosse. The company's products are available in over 45 countries through a network of over 3,700 distributors.  The company acquired the Easton business unit from BRG Sports in April, 2014.
Established in 1927, Performance Sports Group Ltd. (formerly Bauer Performance Sports) designs, manufactures and markets performance sports equipment and related apparel under the leading brands Bauer Hockey, Mission Roller Hockey and Maverik Lacrosse. The company's products are available in over… MoreEstablished in 1927, Performance Sports Group Ltd. (formerly Bauer Performance Sports) designs, manufactures and markets performance sports equipment and related apparel under the leading brands Bauer Hockey, Mission Roller Hockey and Maverik Lacrosse. The company's products are available in over 45 countries through a network of over 3,700 distributors.  The company acquired the Easton business unit from BRG Sports in April, 2014.

2013 and Earlier:
The IT department for Performance Sports Group, also known as Bauer Hockey, operates out of the company's Exeter, NH headquarters. There is also support staff located in Canadian and European offices.

The Business Solutions division is responsible for designing and developing enterprise applications to support global business operations.

The global Project Management Office is responsible for overseeing strategic initiatives and ensuring they are aligned with corporate objectives on a global level.

The rest of the department oversees day-to-day IT infrastructure operations, including telecommunications systems, server administration, desktop support, data protection, network security, and storage area networking.





